===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[moder]]'' ("mother") < Old English ''[[modor|mōdor]]''. Cognates include Modern Greek [[μητέρα]], Latin ''[[mater]]'', German ''[[Mutter]]'' and Russian [[мать]] (mat’).

===Noun===
'''mother''' (''plural:'' '''mothers''')
#<!--DefNWomanIfHasChild--> A woman who has at least one child.
#:''My sister-in-law has just become a mother.''
#<!--DefB--> One's female [[parent]].
#:''I am visiting my mother today.''
<!--"mother of all ..." and "motherfucker" definitions are given separately below because they have different origins--> I love my momy.

